-- Thailand Equity Mover Column: Indorama Ventures, Lohakit Metal
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-06-08T09:50:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/khon-kaen-khonburi-sugar-total-access-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.8 percent to 1,127.10, a one-week
high. The gauge advanced 1.1 percent this week, the first weekly
increase in five.  Indorama Ventures Pcl (IVL)  , the nation’s largest maker
of polyester, jumped 6.7 percent to 28 baht, the steepest
advance since Feb. 15. Cotton futures yesterday rose 5.7 percent
to settle at 72.28 cents a pound in  New York , the biggest gain
since Dec. 8, 2008. Polyester is a substitute for cotton.  Lohakit Metal Pcl (LHK)  , a producer of steel products,
dropped 2.8 percent to 2.56 baht, the largest decline since Feb.
14. Investors who buy the company’s stock from today won’t be
entitled to its cash dividend of 0.14 baht a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
